# Page d'informations serveur

Is an easy-to-use self-hosted monitoring tool.

<img src="https://img.as215772.net/infor_serveur.png" width="700" alt="" />


## üîß How to Install

Requirements:

- Platform
  - ‚úÖ Major Linux distros such as Debian, Ubuntu, CentOS, Fedora and ArchLinux etc.
  - ‚úÖ Windows 10 (x64), Windows Server 2012 R2 (x64) or higher
  - ‚ùå Replit / Heroku
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/download/) 18 / 20.4
- [npm](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/) 9
- [Git](https://git-scm.com/downloads)
- [pm2](https://pm2.keymetrics.io/) - For running Inform-Server in the background

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Tinayeur/inform_server
cd inform_server
npm install

# Option 1. Try it
node server.js

# (Recommended) Option 2. Run in the background using PM2
# Install PM2 if you don't have it:
npm install pm2 -g && pm2 install pm2-logrotate

# Start Server
pm2 start server.js --name inform-server
```

Inform-Server is now running on http://localhost:3000

More useful PM2 Commands

```bash
# If you want to see the current console output
pm2 monit

# If you want to add it to startup
pm2 save && pm2 startup
```
